// @test regression/udf-call-validation
// @description The local checker validated builtin calls but not user-function calls. It now checks arg type (CE10123 on typed primitive params), too-many-args (CE10115), and missing required params (CE10165) against the captured signature - conservatively: non-overloaded UDFs only, count checks gated on a clean parse, typed-primitive params only, names that are also methods skipped. Default params, named args, and exact calls stay clean. Probed 2026-06-25 via pine-lint --tv, see INV095.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=7, message=/Cannot call "f" with argument "x"="hello".*literal string.*series int/
// @expects error: line=8, message=/Too many arguments passed into the "f\(\)" function call.*Passed 2.*expected 1/
// @expects error: line=9, message=/No value assigned to the "b" parameter in g\(\)/
// @expects errors: 3

//@version=6
indicator("udf-call-validation")
f(int x) =>
    x + 1
g(a, b) =>
    a + b
y = f("hello")
z = f(1, 2)
w = g(1)
ok1 = f(5)
ok2 = g(1, 2)
ok3 = f(x = 7)
plot(y + z + w + ok1 + ok2 + ok3)
